Minimize Time to Close Model Template

This article describes the app and associated assets generated by creating a model using the Minimize Time to Close model template.

Use Case: Numerical Use Cases

Prerequisites:
Einstein Discovery checks for minimum requirements, including at least 400 closed won opportunities.
Field access and Salesforce configuration are also required.

Generated Assets:
Model: Minimize Time to Close
Explains factors that drive shorter deal cycles and suggested actions to improve the predicted outcome.
CRM Analytics Dataset: Opportunity Training Dataset
Dataset used to train the machine learning model.
Dashboard: About This Story
Model description, dataset description, rows analyzed, average opportunity age, average predicted time to close, mean absolute error, number of open deals with predictions.

Prediction Definition, Model: Minimize Time to Close, Age
Deployed automatically.
Salesforce Objects:
Account, Opportunity, Opportunity History, Product, Price Book, Task, Event, User, UserRole
Model Outcome Variable and Derived Variables:
Age (Outcome) numeric, # Amount Decreased numeric, # Amount Increased numeric, # Closed Date Pushed numeric, # Completed Activities numeric, # Lost Opportunities on Account numeric, # Won Opportunities on Account numeric, Account Tenure numeric, Owner Tenure text, Top Product Family text, Top Product Name text.
title: Minimizing Deal Cycles with Einstein Discovery
